genresAdvancedInfo.name: starogradska
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Starogradska is a traditional music genre from the Balkans, particularly Serbia and Croatia. It is characterized by its use of folk instruments such as the accordion, tamburica, and violin, and its melancholic melodies and lyrics. Starogradska music is often performed at weddings and other celebrations, and is a beloved part of Balkan cultural heritage.
